 pieces (2 cm)","125 g butter, cut in pieces, plus extra for greasing","100 g plain flour","1 tsp baking powder","600 g water"]},{"title":"Whipped Cream and Chocolate Ganache Filling","content":["315 g whipping cream, chilled","80 g dark chocolate (50% cocoa), cut in pieces (2 cm)"]}],"id":"r150941","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-nCkmFj7Kxzc\/XZWrIO0qGFI\/AAAAAAAAfig\/LOOoQQudxaUdDtb4XzyVMc2-jDo6EJhfQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_cfdJyMYieq02zXxc.png","title":"Steamed Chocolate Cake with Whipped Cream","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10 g","fat":"51 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"45 g","calories":"2863 kJ \/ 684 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round metal cake tin (Ø 20 cm), steaming rack or chopsticks, wire rack, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["<i>This cake is a revelation. You don’t need an oven to create an airy yet rich treat worthy of a pâtisserie. And if you don’t have the right size tin, use the Varoma tray, as described in the variation.<\/i>","A cake tin measuring <nobr>Ø 20 cm<\/nobr> should rest on the sides of the Varoma dish, above the steaming holes. To ensure holes are not blocked, use a steaming rack, <nobr>2 small<\/nobr> chopsticks or a wooden chopstick broken in two to support the cake tin off the bottom of the Varoma dish.","In addition to or instead of ganache filling, add a layer of jam before spreading with whipped cream, then top the cake with seasonal fruit.<br>- Dust the top with cocoa or garnish with chocolate shavings.<br>- Instead of steaming the cake in a tin, use the Varoma tray. Line with baking paper with enough to go <nobr>2 cm<\/nobr> up the sides, and steam for <nobr><strong>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1,<\/strong><\/nobr> or until a skewer inserted in the middle comes out clean. Continue with cooling instructions in <nobr>step 5.<\/nobr> In <nobr>step 6,<\/nobr> use <nobr>300 g cream<\/nobr> instead of <nobr>250 g cream,<\/nobr> to cover the larger surface of the cake."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h